Issue #13880: Support for propertyNames in OpenAPI schema when using dict[Enum, ...] with Pydantic v2

When using dict[StrEnum, ...] or RootModel[dict[StrEnum, ...]] in a FastAPI app with Pydantic v2, the generated OpenAPI schema does not enumerate the enum values used as dictionary keys. Instead, the UI shows [any-key], which does not reflect the actual constraints.

As of Pydantic v2.11+, support for emitting propertyNames with enum constraints was added via [PR #10478](https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic/pull/10478). This allows OpenAPI/JSON Schema to correctly express restrictions on object keys, such as:

```
{
  "type": "object",
  "propertyNames": {
    "type": "string",
    "enum": ["foo", "bar"]
  },
  "additionalProperties": {
    "type": "integer"
  }
}
```

